docs.snippet: Internal Coast Guard documents, obtained by The New York Times, outlined a grim forecast for the small service as a result of the 35-day government shutdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The government shutdown that ended last month has taken a lasting hit on the Coast Guard, which has grounded aircraft, stopped major ship repairs and will leave parts of an air station in Puerto Rico without emergency generators for the start of hurricane season because of a backlog that will take months to process.
